name: It's Alive
description:
24" x 36", 5 color screen print for "It's Alive" at The Alamo Drafthouse in Austin, TX.

It was a lot of fun working on a poster for this Larry Cohen classic. I like my horror movies campy, It's Alive certainly delivers. I may or may not have shed a tear at the end. 

Anyway, I've only got 30 copies to sell here so get 'em while they're hot, movie poster nerds! Signed and numbered by the small hands of Jon Smith.

name: THE WRONG KID DIED(Dewey Cox print)
description:
This is my piece for the Judd Apatow show at Gallery 1988 Melrose.

The concept is a Dewey Cox album cover, 12"x12" screen print WITH hand colored details. I hand painted the pink/red, green and the details and blood splatter on the kid(Dewey's brother, "the wrong kid"...that Dewey accidentally chopped in half).

Signed and numbered edition of just 100.
